title: For Sale:  RUGER® Stainless Super Blackhawk® 44 Mag - 1989
postcontent: We have for auction a New Model Super Blackhawk 44 Magnum revolver. The serial number, U86-20834, tells us this revolver was testfired November 3, 1989. This model, KS45N, did not appear in the Ruger Firearms catalog until 1991. The letter “U” stamped in front of the serial number indicates this revolver is a used firearm. It had been sold to a commercial distributor in November 1989 and then returned to the factory. There are no notes as to why it was returned. This New Model Blackhawk revolver features a wide serrated hammer spur; steel grip frame; stainless finish; 5-1/2” barrel; and walnut grip panels with silver-colored Ruger eagle “SR” logo medallions. Other features include a 6-round capacity 44 Magnum fluted cylinder; a rear sight click-adjustable for windage or elevation, and a Patridge-type front sight mounted on a ramp. This New Model Super Blackhawk revolver will be shipped in the yellow-hinged cardboard box it had been stored in. The revolver is being sold “as is.” The purchaser assumes all liability for its safe and proper ownership, storage, use, and resale. The revolver is a part of the Ruger factory collection in Southport, Connecticut, and a Certificate of Authenticity will be mailed to the winner of the auction.

title: For Sale:  NIB Colt LE6960 CCU
postcontent: It is chambered for the classic 5.56mm NATO (.223 Rem) cartridge and is the first Colt to feature a true midlength gas system. It is lightweight, handy, and very customizeable. This one is a demo gun and in excellent condition. It comes in its original serial matched box, with sealed Colt accessory pack.The CCU features a midlength gas system with a low-profile gas block. This means the block has been moved closer to the muzzle, giving several benefits. For one, it has the same distance and dwell time as a military M4 with a 14.5" barrel. This gives for a smoother recoil impulse, and greater reliability. Also it allows for a longer handguard for grip and attaching accessories. The barrel is 16" long, with a medium-lightweight profile, so it feels great and balances well. It has a 1/7 twist rate, has been MP tested, and is threaded 1/2x28 with a removable A2 birdcage flash hider. There is a milspec M1913 Picatinny rail, which runs the entire length from the charging handle in the back, to out past the gasblock in the front. This means you can mount literally any kind of optic setup you might possibly need no matter what. The upper receiver has a standard forward assist and dustcover, and the lower is rollmarked M4 and Colt's Defense with all proper proofs.
